<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">May 26, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Rebalanced the public articles directory so it no longer reads as puppy-only. Shipped four net-new goat long-form articles, surfaced them at the top of <a href="/articles" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">/articles</a>, and updated the directory hero plus meta description to acknowledge nine-species coverage.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">New articles</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-1 mb-4">
    <li><a href="/articles/dairy-goat-record-keeping-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Dairy Goat Record-Keeping Software</a>. DHIA, Linear Appraisal, parasite-program, herd-health passport, and scrapie compliance covered against the shipped product surface (Breeder Guide &middot; Goats).</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/goat-herd-health-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Goat Herd-Health Software</a>. CAE / CL / Johne&rsquo;s testing, parasite-program rollups, scrapie compliance identifiers, and the legally-locked trust posture (Breeder Guide &middot; Goats).</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/goat-kid-health-guarantee-what-it-covers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Goat Kid Health Guarantee: What It Actually Covers</a>. The four common clause types, herd-level disease-status assurances, scrapie compliance, and dam-raised vs bottle-raised (Buyer Guide &middot; Goats).</li>
    <li><a href="/articles/goat-kid-deposit-and-sale-terms" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Goat Kid Deposit and Sale Terms</a>. Deposits, title transfer, ADGA / AGS / NDGA / MDGA registration mechanics, hold-back arrangements, and the pickup documentation packet (Buyer Guide &middot; Goats).</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Index integration</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The four new goat articles plus the parallel-agent <a href="/articles/goat-kidding-tracking-software" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Goat Kidding Tracking Software</a> piece are surfaced at the top of the article list with a <code>Breeder Guide &middot; Goats</code> and <code>Buyer Guide &middot; Goats</code> tag pattern. Hero subhead and BaseLayout meta description now reference dogs, cats, horses, goats, rabbits, sheep, alpacas, llamas, and cattle by name. The existing 14 dog-coded and species-neutral articles remain intact.</p>

  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-4 mb-2">Why the existing puppy and litter articles were not neutralized</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Those four pieces are targeted SEO for specific dog-buyer queries. Neutralizing them would reduce coverage of both species rather than balance the directory. The fix was additive: produce real goat content that competes for goat queries, not subtractive. Status doc: <code>docs/research/goat-audit/2026-05-25/demo-execution/next-17-goat-articles-and-content-directory-status.md</code> in the <code>breederhq</code> repo.</p>
